Assembler Syntax

MSUB.S aed0..15(opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vt), aed0..15(opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vs), aed0..15(opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vr)

C Syntax

#include <xtensa/tie/xt_FP.h>

extern void XT_MSUB_S(xtfloat a /*inout*/, xtfloat b, xtfloat c);

Description

(please consult the Xtensa ® Instruction Set Architecture Reference Manual for any cross references and additional information)

Using IEEE754 single-precision arithmetic, MSUB.S multiplies the corresponding halves of data registers frs and frt, subtracts the products from the corresponding halves of data register frr, and then writes the differences back to each corresponding half of data register frr. The computation is performed with no intermediate round.

Operation

For each corresponding half: 

AE_DR[r] ← AE_DR[r] -S (AE_DR[s] ×S AE_DR[t]) (×Sdoes not round)

FSR[StatusFlags: VOUI] ← Or in update

Exceptions

  • EveryInst Group
  • GenExcep(Coprocessor0Disabled) if Coprocessor Context Option

Implementation Pipeline

In Out
InvalidFlag Wstage+2, OverflowFlag Wstage+2, UnderflowFlag Wstage+2, InexactFlag Wstage+2, RoundMode Mstage, opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vt Mstage, opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vs Mstage, opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vr Mstage InvalidFlag Wstage+2, OverflowFlag Wstage+2, UnderflowFlag Wstage+2, InexactFlag Wstage+2, opnd_vfpu2_sem_spfma_vt Wstage+2
